                            <strong>Core Challenge:</strong> Traditional pedigree relationships give expected values, but actual genomic sharing varies substantially due to Mendelian sampling and linkage.
                            
                            <ul>
                                <li>Existing formulae were scattered and incomplete for different relationship types</li>
                                <li>No unified framework existed for computing variances across all relationship types</li>
                                <li>Genomic selection and GWAS require understanding of actual vs. expected relationships</li>
                                <li>Need to quantify uncertainty in relationship inference from genomic data</li>
                            </ul>
                            
                            <strong>Applications:</strong> Critical for genomic selection, relationship inference, GWAS quality control, and estimating inbreeding depression.
                        </div>
